# Naming Conventions

## File Naming
- React components: PascalCase (e.g., `TableOfContents.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (e.g., `useTabDetection.ts`)
- Utility files: kebab-case (e.g., `theme-initializer.ts`)
- Test files: Same name as the file they test with `.test.ts` suffix

## Code Naming
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `export const TableOfContents = () => {}`)
- Functions: camelCase (e.g., `export const getHeadings = () => {}`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for truly constant values
- Types/Interfaces: PascalCase with descriptive names (e.g., `type EditorProps = {}`)
- Atoms: camelCase with `Atom` suffix (e.g., `contentAtom`)
